- A framework is a semi-complete applications, providing reusable/common structure to share amount applications.
Developers extend the framework to their specific needs.

- JUnit features
  * separate test class instances and class loaders for each test to avoid side-effects
  * JUnit annotations to provide resource initialization and reclamation methods: @Before, @BeforeClass, @After,
  and @AfterClass
  * a variety of assert methods to easily check results of tests
  * popular tools integration
